  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil half a kettle</p><p>Cut the <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into bite-sized pieces</p><p>Top, tail and slice the <strong>carrots</strong> finely</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped potato </strong>and<strong> sliced carrot</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong>, bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for 10-12 min or until fork-tender</p><p>Once cooked, drain and return to the pot to steam-dry</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-copy-1660037942661-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-copy-1660037942661-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-copy-1660037942661-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-copy-1660037942661-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-copy-1660037942661-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Combine the <strong>turkey</strong> <strong>mince</strong> with<strong> half </strong>the <strong>chicken stock mix</strong> (you'll use the rest later) and a generous pinch of <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Mix thoroughly with clean hands until fully combined, then shape into 12 <span class=\"text-danger\">[24]</span> <strong>meatballs</strong></p><p>Reboil half a kettle</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>over a medium heat</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-copy-1660037946433-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-copy-1660037946433-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-copy-1660037946433-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-copy-1660037946433-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-copy-1660037946433-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once hot, add the <strong>meatballs</strong> to the pan and cook for 2 min, turning occasionally, until they are browned on most sides</p><p>Meanwhile, combine the <strong>remaining chicken</strong> <strong>stock mix</strong>, <strong>Dijon mustard</strong>, <strong>soy sauce</strong> and<strong> redcurrant jelly</strong> in 300ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[600ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> – this is your <strong>stock</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>dried cranberries</strong> to a bowl and cover them with <strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Transfer the <strong>browned</strong> <strong>meatballs</strong> to a plate</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-copy-1660038004774-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-copy-1660038004774-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-copy-1660038004774-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-copy-1660038004774-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-copy-1660038004774-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the pan to a medium heat with a small knob of <strong>butter</strong>, add 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span><strong> flour</strong> and stir until sandy</p><p>Whisk the <strong>stock</strong> into the flour</p><p>Cook for 2-3 min until the stock has thickened slightly</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-copy-1660038012232-x200.jpg",
