            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-copy-1660038012232-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the sauce thickens, chop the<strong> dill</strong> finely, including the stalks</p><p>Add most of the<strong> chopped dill</strong> (save the rest for garnish!) to the thickened sauce, return the <strong>browned</strong> <strong>meatballs</strong> to the pan</p><p>Cook, covered, for 6 min further or until the meatballs are cooked through (no pink meat!) and the sauce has thickened to a gravy-like consistency – these are your <strong>Swedish-style turkey meatballs & gravy</strong></p>",
